709544f-a.text:

709549f-b.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 49th Street (West)
709549f-b.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from West 49th Street, showing the
Sixth Avenue ''El'' and its 50th Street station at Rockefeller
(Radio) City.
The R.C. A. Building occupies the 49th to 50th Street
frontage, while the R.K. O. Builoing is above, on the 50th
to 5lst block. Note the southbound train stopping for passengers.
This is one of the last tfips, as shortly the line is to be dis-
continued and the structure razed.
View No. 2 is eastward on 50th Street and shows the wooden
sides of this station silhouetted against the 70 story R. C. A.
Building.
March 1w39
Viewsc 1-2
Wm. Herries
MAY BE REPRODUCED

709551f-b.text:

cleared area in the foreground (50th - 49th Stis.) will

Several years later (1940) the adjoining U. S. Ruhher
